1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:12,000
🎙️ EduLens AI — Refined Demo

2
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:24,000
Part 1: The Hook — Most EdTech today has a 'Shallow Learning' problem. We built an Explain-First platform that decodes a student's mental model.

3
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:46,000
Part 2: The "Explain-First" Challenge — Student view. Instead of multiple-choice, the student explains Photosynthesis in their own words.

4
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:58,000
Student types: "Plants use sunlight to make oxygen so that humans and animals can breathe." The AI will evaluate this explanation.

5
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:12,000
AI feedback: Identifies this as Incomplete Understanding. Notes the student focused on oxygen and missed glucose/energy production. Bloom's level: Remembering.

6
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:26,000
Part 3: Mastery Tools — Navigate the Knowledge Graph. Each interaction updates the graph and shows mastered concepts and prerequisites.

7
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:36,000
Open the EduLens Assistant (Chatbot). It uses Socratic prompts to help students bridge gaps without giving answers away.

8
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:56,000
Part 4: The Live Classroom — Educator Dashboard. Teachers see aggregated Misconception Heatmaps and can click "Go Live" for a real-time feed using WebSockets.

9
00:01:56,000 --> 00:02:00,000
Intervention Queue flags struggling students so teachers can step in immediately.

10
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:20,000
Conclusion: EduLens AI understands students, not just scores. Thanks for watching.
